\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a facility location game there are number of players located at different
 locations and a number of facilities needs to be located.
 Each player has a utility function based on his location and the facilities
 locations.
 A mechanism recieves the players locations and decides the facilities locations
 while trying to maximise the social cost: the sum of the players utilities.
 The players can lie about their location in order to increase their utility.
 An algorithm is called thruthfull if each players can't increase his own
 utility by lying.
 Using the Vickrey-Clarke-Groves (VCG) algorithm we get a truthfull optimal
 algorithm by choosing the payments wisely.
 In this problem though, we don't want to take money from people, and therefore
 we search for truthfull appromixation algorithms.
\end_layout

